    "plan_content": "The plan is written and ready for your review at `/Users/timpietrusky/.claude/plans/humming-sprouting-lampson.md`. Here's a summary of everything that will be implemented:\n\n---\n\n## Plan Summary: Stepper Compound Component\n\n### 6 New Files\n| File | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `apps/v4/registry/new-york-v4/ui/stepper.tsx` | Primary styled component |\n| `apps/v4/registry/new-york-v4/examples/stepper-demo.tsx` | Demo (vertical 3-step wizard) |\n| `apps/v4/registry/bases/base/ui/stepper.tsx` | Base-UI registry variant |\n| `apps/v4/registry/bases/base/examples/stepper-example.tsx` | Base-UI showcase example |\n| `apps/v4/registry/bases/radix/ui/stepper.tsx` | Radix registry variant |\n| `apps/v4/registry/bases/radix/examples/stepper-example.tsx` | Radix showcase example |\n\n### 6 Registry Entry Additions (edits to existing `_registry.ts` files)\nOne insert each ŌĆö alphabetically between \"spinner\" and \"switch\" ŌĆö in all three systems' `ui/` and `examples/` registries.\n\n---\n\n### Component Architecture\n\n**No external dependencies** ŌĆö pure React + HTML, no Radix or Base-UI primitive needed.\n\n**Two React contexts:**\n- `StepperContext` ŌĆö root; holds `value: number`, `onValueChange`, `orientation`\n- `StepperItemContext` ŌĆö per-step; holds `step: number` + derived `state: \"active\" | \"completed\" | \"pending\"` (computed by comparing integers, no registration mechanism)\n\n**7 sub-components:** `Stepper` ┬Ę `StepperItem` ┬Ę `StepperTrigger` ┬Ę `StepperTitle` ┬Ę `StepperDescription` ┬Ę `StepperSeparator` ┬Ę `StepperContent`\n\n**Orientation strategy** (follows `tabs.tsx` exactly):\n- `data-orientation` attribute on root + `group/stepper` CSS group\n- Children use `group-data-[orientation=horizontal]/stepper:` and `group-data-[orientation=vertical]/stepper:` selectors\n- Separator becomes `h-px` (horizontal) or `w-px self-stretch` (vertical)\n\n**State styling** via `data-state` on `StepperItem` + `group-data-[state=active]/stepper-item:` selectors on child indicator circles ŌĆö consistent with accordion, toggle-group patterns.\n\n**Bases variants** are identical in logic to new-york-v4, differing only in the `cn` import path (`@/registry/bases/base/lib/utils` vs `@/registry/bases/radix/lib/utils`). The bases example files use the `ExampleWrapper` + `Example` wrapper pattern.",
